parameters:
Tsugumi is squatting alone in the middle of the road to the
beach.

She's wearing a swimsuit, but no matter where I look, I
can't see any traces of it being wet with water.

She was just absentmindedly gazing at the sea. They didn't
notice me until I approached closely.
Tsugumi? What were you doing here?
I was just gazing at the sea.
The sea? Where the waves are swaying?

Waves... Yes, that's right. Just gazing at them makes me feel
good too.
Anyway, is it okay if I stay by your side?
Well, feel free to do as you please.
Is it fun being with me?
What are you saying? It's obviously fun.

Even though I'm not very gentle and I'm not good at
talking,
Isn't it boring? Being with someone like me.
Why are you worried about things like that,
If it wasn't fun, I wouldn't be with you, idiot.
What's wrong today? You seem energetic.
Sometimes I dig a hole by myself and just crawl into it...
Do you still hate girls like me?
I didn't say I hate you,
Then, may I be spoiled a little longer?

Tsugumi gently rested her head on my shoulder while saying
that.
While listening to the sound of the waves coming and going
I gazed at her deep blue hair, like the sea.

Her hair, which was braided into a round shape, looked
like a soda-flavored pudding.
I'll give it a little push
No, it was just a mistake.

Do you think it's okay to carelessly touch a girl's hair
like a toy?

Well, they seemed in a bad mood, so I wanted to cheer them
up with the energy of the super handsome Hikaru-sama.
Pfft, what's that? An imitation of Kanae?

Ugh... We had such a good vibe going, but thanks to Hikaru,
it's all ruined now, isn't it?

Tsugumi, your hairstyle that looks like a sweet bun is very
cute.
...Did you like this way of braiding?
Eh...? Well, I don't dislike it.

...If Hikaru is okay with it, I don't mind if you touch me a
little more.
Eh? What did you say just now?
No, let's endure it after all.
...What is it, staring at someone like that?
No, I was just looking. Is it not allowed to look?
......It's not that it's not allowed, but...
I watched the waves with Tsugumi for a while.

When you look at me like that, even I feel a little
embarrassed.
I'll give it a little push
No, it was just a slip of the tongue.

Do you think it's okay to carelessly touch a girl's hair
like a toy?

Nah~, I heard you were in a bad mood, so I wanted to cheer
up the super handsome Hikaru-sama.
Huh, what's that? An imitation of Kanae?

Ugh... We had such a good flow going, but thanks to Hikaru,
it's all ruined, isn't it?

Tsugumi, your hairstyle that looks like a sweet bun is very
cute.
...Did you like this kind of hairstyle?
Eh...? Well, I don't dislike it.

...If Hikaru is okay with it, I don't mind if you touch me a
little more.
Eh? What did you say just now?
No, let's endure it after all.
No, I was just looking. Is it not okay to look?
......It's not that it's not okay, but...
I watched the waves with Tsugumi for a while.

After spending time like that, she started running towards
the cottage.
She seemed strangely embarrassed for some reason...

When I think about it, the shoulder that was in contact
with her felt hot.
It feels like her body temperature is still lingering.
It's true that I did something embarrassing...

After being blown by the sea breeze for a while, I returned
to the cottage after experiencing a sentimental mood.

The waves that come and go crash against my feet, turning
into white foam.

When I welcomed the pleasantly ticklish waves, memories of
last year's summer training camp came to mind.

It was a summer that was a little later than now, a time
when the sound of cicadas filled the empty space.
Why are you all alone in a place like this?
Hey, you know, Tsugumi was like this the other day.
Oh, was that so? I forgot.
Is this that pattern? Is it that pattern?
Next, you... say Excuse me, it was intentional!
Haha, I already have you figured out.
Nuh, are you a child? You're so immature, Hikaru.

They looked just like a child, pouting their cheeks and
averting their gaze.

It was tough trying to calm her down until we returned to
the cottage later.
It's their own fault, isn't it?
